fabric/operations.py
fabric/sftp.py
==================
03a4be3;Erich Heine;2010-03-26 14:14:27 -0500;Crazy refactoring: added an ftp object
So this is a much bigger commit than I really would like, but It is one
logical change. I changed the working put/get stuff, and added a new
file: sftp.py. This basically does 2 different things:

1. takes advantage of other fabric goodness
2. adds good file stuff to sftp. (i dont know why it isnt there anyway).

The constructor just takes a host string, and then you can do all sorts
of cool file stuff via sftp, like exists, and walk, and so on. This
really adds a lot of functionality to the whole thing.

In this commit there is also an auto test-runner. If
test_scp/fabfile.py:testall runs without erroring, sftp works fine.
There may be edge cases missing, but this keeps most cases happy.

==

