6d46ca6;Jeff Forcier;2009-10-25 20:28:05 -0400;Make normalize() behave better for empty input.
Technically an empty input could be considered an error condition, but
since this is an inner subroutine designed to just transform a string
into a tuple, returning empty strings is arguably more correct.
Certainly easier to deal with.

