fabfile.py
fabric/main.py
fabric/network.py
==================
343530b;Jeff Forcier;2009-05-12 17:07:15 -0400;Lots of fussing with contextmanagers, including output control ones.
* env.abort_on_failure is now simply env.warn_only
* warnings_only() contextmanager removed (for now) in favor of just using
  setenv(warn_only=True)
* setenv() lets you set 1..N env values within a block
* settings() lets you do that, plus combine other contextmanagers (using
  contextlib.nested)
* new hide()/show() contextmanagers for controlling state.output stuff

