fabric/main.py
fabric/network.py
==================
fb03726;Jeff Forcier;2009-05-10 19:39:12 -0400;Removed TODO about searching harder for fabfiles if first has no callables.
It sounds like a neat idea, but it's messy: a loaded fabfile might still modify
the env, or do other things, at load time, so if we load it, find it has no
valid callables, and then load another, the first fabfile will still have
altered things.

Given that the original TODO concerned what was already an edge case (first
found fabfile not having any external callables) probably best to just leave
things as they are: first fabfile is loaded, and we abort if it has no good
callables.

Largest commit message size / changeset size ratio ever?

