fabric/state.py
==================
f550f67;Jeff Forcier;2009-04-30 11:47:22 -0400;Fix host regex to be more open (anything but a semicolon).
Symptom was that it wasn't catching hyphens; rather than keep tacking on
exceptions, realized what I really meant was "anything at all, except a
semicolon, which is not a legal hostname char anyway, and signifies a port
number".

