fabric.py
==================
749c908;Jeff Forcier;2008-07-14 18:21:30 -0400;Big changes to connections/hosts.
1. Connections are now naively created/destroyed per command.
2. Hosts can be specified per-command with @hosts.
3. @run_per_host => @connects, specifies that an operation executes remotely.
4. No connections are attempted for local-only commands.

==

fabric.py
==================
10c47d5;Jeff Forcier;2008-07-14 13:42:15 -0400;Makes fab_mode applicable per-command via 'mode' decorator.
This allows not only more granular control over what mode is used for
what command, but enables users to set fab_mode="deep" globally without causing
built-in commands like help() to run multiple times (since I have set those builtins
to be explicitly "broad").

Given that I don't see too many realistic options for the value of "mode" this may
make more sense to implement as two separate @broad and @deep decorators, we'll see.

==

