29c5223;Jeff Forcier;2008-07-12 22:04:28 -0400;Update capture behavior to return two-tuple (stdout + success boolean).
Allows failure code to work normally. Users can still override failure handling
with fail=(ignore|warn) in cases where they want output from a command that
may still have a nonzero return code (e.g. using grep to test for existence
of something).

